premise_source_doc_sentence: Chauncey Hollis , Jr.  (  born May 21 , 1987  )  better known by his stage name Hit-Boy is an American record producer and hip hop recording artist from Fontana , California .
In May 2011 , Hollis had signed a deal with Kanye West 's GOOD Music production wing , known as Very G.O.O.D. Beats and left the label after his contract expired in June 2013 .
In December 2012 , it was revealed he had signed a recording contract with Interscope Records , and subsequently founded his own record label imprint , Hits Since ' 87 .

He is perhaps best known for his production catalog , which includes `` Niggas in Paris '' by Jay-Z and Kanye West , `` Drop the World '' by Lil Wayne and Eminem , and the GOOD Music single `` Clique '' , all of which have been certified platinum or higher by the Recording Industry Association of America  (  RIAA  )  .
